All tasks complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:

## Changes Made

### New Files
1. **`internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`** — Fan-out log broadcaster that manages per-run subscriber channels. Thread-safe, non-blocking publish with 256-entry buffer per subscriber. Supports Subscribe/Unsubscribe/Publish/Finish lifecycle.

2. **`internal/logstream/broadcaster_test.go`** — 12 tests covering subscribe/publish, multiple subscribers, isolated runs, unsubscribe, finish, subscribe-after-finish, concurrent access, and slow subscriber behavior.

3. **`internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go`** — 6 tests covering SSE for completed runs (serves full.log), active runs (live streaming), run-not-found, no-broadcaster fallback, full.log line parsing, and completed runs with no full.log.

### Modified Files
4. **`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** — Added `logBroadcast` field to `ClocheServer`. In `trackRun()`, all lines from container stdout are now broadcast to subscribers (JSON protocol messages are parsed to `LogLine` format, non-JSON lines forwarded as script output). Added `LogBroadcaster()` accessor and `protocolToLogLine()` converter. `Finish()` called when container output ends.

5. **`internal/adapters/web/handler.go`** — Added `logBroadcast` field and `WithLogBroadcaster()` option. Added `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` SSE endpoint that streams live log data for active runs (via broadcaster subscription) or serves archived `full.log` for completed runs. Includes `parseFullLogLine()` regex parser.

6. **`internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`** — Added log viewer section with auto-scrolling `<pre>` container. Uses `EventSource` API to connect to SSE endpoint. Color-codes entries by type (status=blue, llm=green, script=default). Shows "Live" badge while streaming, "Complete" when finished.

7. **`internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`** — Added `.log-viewer`, `.log-line`, and `.log-type-*` CSS classes for the log viewer with dark mode support.

8. **`cmd/cloche/main.go`** — Added `--follow`/`-f` flag to `cloche logs` command. When set, connects to the daemon's SSE endpoint via HTTP and prints color-coded log lines (blue for status, green for LLM) in real-time. Uses `CLOCHE_HTTP` env var for daemon address (defaults to `localhost:8080`).

9. **`cmd/cloched/main.go`** — Wires the gRPC server's `LogBroadcaster()` into the web handler via `WithLogBroadcaster()`.

### SSE Event Format
```json
{"timestamp":"2026-03-03T10:15:00Z","type":"status","content":"step_started: build"}
```
With a terminal `event: done` when the stream completes.

CLOCHE_RESULT:success
